I. List of file
=========
VMI Tools:
    policy_engine.c
    policy_engine.h
    repair_engine.h
    Makefile.in

Linux kernel modules:
    repair_driver.c
    repair_driver.h
    close_file_module.c
    killsocket_module.c
    ps_deescalate_module.c
    psaction_module.c
    sled_object_module.c
    start_process_module.c
    system_map_reset.c
    trusted_load_module.c
    Makefile

CLIPS Files:
    application_knowledge.cls
    recovery_contructs.cls

II. Build  instructions for the VMI tools.
    1. Download the source for CLIPS verion 6.24 from http://clipsrules.sourceforge.net  and copy it to /opt directory 
    2. Copy  Makefile.in to the vmi/tools directory. This make file contains commands to compile the policy_engine along with the other tools in that /tools directory. 
    3. Copy the VMI tools listed above to the vmi/tools directory.
    4. Run "make" in vmi-obj/tools directory to compile all the tools.

III. Build instructions for the kernel modules.
    1. Boot a linux DomU image. Preferably the same versions as the domO. I am currently using linux 3.8.0
    2. Copy all the Linux kernel modules listed above into a temporary directory in DomU.
    3. Run "make" , "make modules_install" and "depmod"
    4. Load the main driver module: "insmod repair_driver.ko"

IV. Execution instructions.
    1. Copy the application_knowledge.cls and recovery_contructs.cls file to the vmi-obj/tools directory.
    2. Create a new directory vmi-obj/tools/state_information. This directory is for storing file with temp state information. These temp files will be automatically created.
    3. Execute the policy using this command :
       sudo LD_LIBRARY_PATH=/opt/vmi/elfutils/lib:/opt/vmi/glib/lib:/us/local/lib:/usr/lib:/opt/clips/clips-6.24/clipssrc gdb --args ./policy_engine -m ubuntu
    4. The tool runs once in every WAIT_TIME number of seconds. 

